Suspended Western Cape Community Safety MEC Albert Fritz has been fired by Premier Alan Winde. eNCA speaks to Winde for more. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Suspended Western Cape Community Safety MEC Albert Fritz has been fired by Premier Alan Winde. An independent investigation has found that there is sufficient credibility in the allegations of sexual misconduct. WATCH | DA WCape leader Albert Fritz steps down In January, Fritz stepped down as the provincial leader of the DA in the Western Cape. Fritz was also suspended from his role as MEC for Community Safety.